  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the name Ainsley?",
  "response": "The name **Ainsley** is of Old English origin, derived from the elements \"\u0101n\" meaning \"one\" or \"solitary\" and \"l\u0113ah\" meaning \"wood,\" \"clearing,\" or \"meadow.\" Therefore, the name Ainsley can be interpreted to mean **\"one's meadow\"** or **\"solitary clearing.\"**\n\nIt is a unisex name, though it has been more commonly used for girls in recent years, particularly in English-speaking countries. Ainsley has a gentle, nature-inspired quality, making it a popular choice for parents seeking a name with both historical roots and a soft, modern feel.",
